cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.DB, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with the construction of a graph data structure for DNA fragment assembly and shortest superstring computation, which are problems in computational biology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of the graph for DNA fragment assembly and shortest superstring computation also relates to cs.DB (Databases) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
